article.headline: Longhorns force 28 turnovers in rout
article.linkText: Bowers, Reed lift No. 21 Texas over Texas-Arlington
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas -- Kala Bowers and Coco Reed each scored 20 points Wednesday night to lead (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) Texas to a 73-44 victory over
Texas-Arlington.

	   Reed was 7-of-9 from the field and 6-of-8 from the free throw
line, while Bowers was 7-of-10 from the field.

	   Sloppy ball-handling by the Lady Mavs (2-5) led to 28 turnovers.
The Longhorns (5-2) scored 29 points off the turnovers.

	   Texas-Arlington led 12-10 with 13:24 to go in the half before
the Longhorns went on a 21-7 run to take the lead for good at
31-17. Reed had six points and Bowers had five points and three
rebounds in the run.

	   The Longhorns shot 78 percent from the field in the first half
while holding Texas-Arlington to 36 percent. The performance was
one of the top five shooting halves in Texas' history.

	   For the game, the Longhorns shot 57 percent from the field,
while Texas-Arlington finished at 32 percent.

	   Chronda Hawkins led Texas-Arlington with 14 points.

	   Stacy Stephens added 13 points and eight rebounds for Texas.

	   This was the first meeting between the schools in 20 years.
